# About the Author

## Name
Kishan Singh

## Background
I am an independent student researcher from India coming from a rural farming background. 
My academic journey has been shaped by resilience, self-learning, and strong interest in Mathematics and Physics.

## Academic Record
- Scored around 90% in Class 10
- Scored 73.6% in Class 12 despite a serious accident during examination period
- Among Top 20 Percentile students in the board examination

## Achievement
- State Rank 35 in LIC Olympiad (Class 6) among 57,000+ students
- Newspaper recognition based on Class 10 academic performance

## Research Experience
Developed an independent research project connecting computational thinking with environmental sustainability (SUPGS model).

Received academic feedback and encouragement from:
- Professors at National University of Singapore (NUS)
- Professors at IIT Kanpur
- Researchers from Chinese universities
- Appreciation communication from NIF (India)

## Research Interest
- Computer Science
- Computational Modeling
- Sustainable Systems
- Environment and Technology Integration

## Goal
To pursue Computer Science research and contribute to practical, scalable solutions for real-world environmental challenges.
